race.comment: IMMORTALISED (2) has been building to a win, the latest running on hard to just miss by a nose. Looks well placed here and can go one better. TITANIC (1) was well in the market on debut at Stawell and after getting back found the line strongly for a close-up fourth. Has upside and expected to go close again. BUNDORAN (8) has been given time to get off a strong fresh-up run when runner-up at Ararat. That was first run in nine months and will be much better for it. Has to be included.  MOSQUITO AWARD (10) is a daughter of Shamus Award from Is It A Mosquito on debut. From a good family including the dual Group 3 winner Swats That. Showing ability at the trials and expected to run a bold race at first outing.
